sentences.english: It takes away our edge, makes us groggy, and disrupts our sleep.
sentences.chinese: 它让我们反应迟钝，头昏脑胀，扰乱我们的睡眠。

sentences.english: Look at my schedule make my head spin.
sentences.chinese: 看日程表就使我头昏脑胀。

sentences.english: The whisky got into his head.
sentences.chinese: 威士忌使他醉得头晕脑胀。

sentences.english: The very idea sets my head reeling .
sentences.chinese: 就是那念头把我弄得头昏脑胀。

sentences.english: I'm going from place to place.
sentences.chinese: 在地方之间周循使我头昏脑胀。

sentences.english: Awareness alone an important figure in the head on the exchange, incomprehensible.
sentences.chinese: 光是认识重要人物，就寒暄得头昏脑胀，不知所云。

sentences.english: Even if he was disorientated then, he should apologize for his behaviour NOW.
sentences.chinese: 即使他头昏脑胀，那么现在他也该向她道歉了。

sentences.english: The condensation shorts the circuits to your brain, and you get all woozy.
sentences.chinese: 湿气凝结导致大脑短路，你开始头昏脑胀。

sentences.english: Even the coconut trees seemed swollen and expectant.
sentences.chinese: 连椰子树都似乎憋得头昏脑胀，巴望能舒上一口气。

sentences.english: The mysterious letters had made Sophie's head spin.
sentences.chinese: 这两封神秘的信把苏菲搅得头晕脑胀。

sentences.english: My brain is a bit addled by whiskey.
sentences.chinese: 威士忌搞得我头晕脑胀的。

sentences.english: Lack of sleep had fogged her mind.
sentences.chinese: 缺乏睡眠使她头昏脑胀。

sentences.english: The people here seem to be used to the dizzy noise.
sentences.chinese: 这里的人们似乎都习惯于令人头昏脑胀的噪音。

sentences.english: A great number of math exercises make my head swim.
sentences.chinese: 大量的数学作业搞得我头昏脑胀。

swelling of the head (physical condition)/fig. swellheaded/conceited
variant of 頭暈腦脹|头晕脑胀[tou2 yun1 nao3 zhang4]
to faint with blurred vision (idiom); dizzy and eyes dimmed
